VTamil songs on veena
p3
sVnews
p4
VS aliamangalam G. Ramadoss, Kanchi Kamakoti asthana vidwan, presented a veena concert at the 55th monthly music festival of the Tiruchi Tamizh Isai Sangam at the Sangam premises, Tiruchi.This was the maiden full-fledged music concert using instruments held under the auspices of the Tiruchi Tamizh Isai Sangam. He was ably supported by Thanjai Sankarasubramanian on the mridangam, Pudukottai Solaimalai on the ghatam and Vishnupuram K. Raghu on morsing.Its originProf. N. Vijayasundari of the Department of Tamil, Urumu Dhanalakshmi College, Tiruchi, was the chief guest.She spoke at length on the origin of the Tamil music and how the Tamizh Isai Moovar promoted the same. It is the duty of every Tamil to follow in the footsteps of the Isai Moovar in protecting and promoting music, she added.L.N. Lakshmanan, industrialist and president of the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, in his presidential address, explained the various activities of the Sangam to promote Tamil music in this part of the state.N. Mohan, vice-president of the Sangam, and others spoke on the occasion.
